<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <% include ../partials/head %>
    <title>Assay: Make your site better</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Assay: Tools for experimenting with, and troubleshooting, a website's UI code">
</head>
<body>

    <% include ../partials/navBar %>

        <div class="container main">

            <div class="jumbotron jumbotron-fluid mt-2 mb-3">
                <div class="container">
                    <h1 class="display-3">Make your site better &amp;&amp; Debug with Friends</h1>
                    <p class="lead">Tools for experimenting with, and troubleshooting, a website's UI code</p>

                    <a href=" /get-started" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-lg float-xs-right mr-3 mt-2">
                       Get Started
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 mb-2">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div style="background-image:url('/images/abstract-q-g-640-216-10.jpg'); min-height:3rem;">
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-block">
                            <h4 class="card-title">Live Sites - Private Edits</h4>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                Assay is a benevolent “man in the middle” that allows for collaborative development
                                and experimentation. One person can make a change to a site and invite others to
                                preview the result.
                            </p>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                Possible uses include:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Rapid bug fixing</li>
                                <li>Proof of Concepts</li>
                                <li>Cross Browser Preview</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 mb-2">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div style="background-image:url('/images/abstract-q-g-640-216-10.jpg'); min-height:3rem;">
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-block">
                            <h4 class="card-title">Invite friends</h4>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                Provides a clean sandbox for multiple people to work with the live site and make
                                changes without having to go through the entire build/deploy/wait cylcle.
                            </p>

                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row mb-2">
                <div class="col-xs-12">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div style="background-image:url('/images/abstract-q-g-640-216-10.jpg'); min-height:3rem;">
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-block">
                            <h4 class="card-title">Automated Experiments</h4>
                            <div class="card-text">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        Speed Mobile delivery by replacing image tags with HTML 5 Picture tags
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                       Deliver the "right size" image for a page
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Speed rendering with JavaScript optimization experiments
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        Lower page weight with CSS optimization
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

